*Abdulsalami peace committee urges INEC, security agencies to Adhere to their constitutional roles By Adedayo Akinwale in Abuja The National Peace Committee headed by former Head of State, General Abdulsalami Abubakar, has called on the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) and the security agencies to adhere strictly to their constitutional roles during the elections. Abubakar made the call Wednesday at the second signing ceremony of the peace accord by the presidential candidates ahead of the February 16 elections. He also called on the party supporters and citizens to refrain from violence or any act that might in any way jeopardise the collective vision of a free, fair, transparent and credible elections Details laterâ€¦